SIMPLE: placket
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Placket
<hw>Plack"et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>plaquer</ets> to lay or clap on. See <er>Placard</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A petticoat, esp. an under petticoat; hence, a cant
term for a woman.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Beau. &
Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The opening or slit left in a petticoat or skirt for
convenience in putting it on; -- called also <altname>placket
hole</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A woman's pocket.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Placoderm</ent>⟦br⟧
